{
  "document_id": "job-22",
  "title": "Job 22",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-heading-eliphaz-speaks:-job’",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Eliphaz Speaks: Job’s Wickedness Is Great"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Can a mortal be of use to God?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Is it any pleasure to the Almighty if you are righteous,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Is it for your piety that he reproves you"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Is not your wickedness great?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "For you have exacted pledges from your family for no reason"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "You have given no water to the weary to drink,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "The powerful possess the land,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "You have sent widows away empty-handed,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Therefore snares are around you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "or darkness so that you cannot see;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "“Is not God high in the heavens?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Therefore you say, ‘What does God know?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "Thick clouds enwrap him, so that he does not see,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Will you keep to the old way"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "They were snatched away before their time;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "They said to God, ‘Leave us alone,’"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "Yet he filled their houses with good things—"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "The righteous see it and are glad;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "saying, ‘Surely our adversaries are cut off,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "“Agree with God, and be at peace;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Receive instruction from his mouth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "If you return to the Almighty, you will be restored,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "if you treat gold like dust"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "and if the Almighty is your gold"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "then you will delight yourself in the Almighty"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "You will pray to him, and he will hear you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "You will decide on a matter, and it will be established for you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "When others are humiliated, you say it is pride,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-22-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "He will deliver even those who are guilty;"
    }
  ]
}